    "body": "### Problem\n\nModifier keys like `<C-3>`, `<M-C-3>`, etc, no longer work after a4c9247 in XTerm(402) or tmux 3.5a.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\nopen xterm\nnvim --clean\ni\n<C-V><M-C-3>\n```\nSee unexpected\n```\n<M-Esc>\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nTo see\n```\n<M-C-3>\n```\n\nThe following naive and probably incorrect patch restores the expected behaviour:\n```\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/tui/tui.c b/src/nvim/tui/tui.c\nindex 0540734e1f..488a714f83 100644\n--- a/src/nvim/tui/tui.c\n+++ b/src/nvim/tui/tui.c\n@@ -2399,6 +2399,8 @@ static void augment_terminfo(TUIData *tui, const char *term, int vte_version, in\n     tui->input.key_encoding = kKeyEncodingXterm;\n   }\n \n+  tui_set_key_encoding(tui);\n+\n   xfree(xterm_version);\n }\n \n```\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-130ef73e3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nnixos unstable\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nXTerm(402)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\ncustom nixpkgs overlay",
